patts-upg
=========

Simple tool to upgrade PATTS databases.

To Build
--------

First, you must install libpatts. You can [download it from Delwink][1] or
through your package manager if your operating system has a package for it.

After installing libpatts, you can take the following steps:

    $ ./autogen.sh
    $ ./configure
    $ make

The program will be compiled and runnable in the current directory.

To Install
----------

After following the build instructions above, you can run

    # make install

to install it to the system.

Usage
-----

patts-upg has a simple command-line interface. You can use the CLI options to
set details, or patts-upg will ask you for any additional information it needs
to perform the upgrade.

See `patts-upg --help` for a full list of options.

Hacking
-------

patts-upg uses the GNU coding style for C with a strict 79-column limit. Tabs
in indentation may be used in place of 8 spaces.

